comment: Beverley (HOU) sets the screen on Gee (NOP) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gee (NOP) cleanly strips the ball from Ariza (HOU).
Ariza's (HOU) shot attempt makes contact with the rim and the shot clock is correctly reset.
Gee (NOP) and Ariza (HOU) make incidental contact with one another away from the ball.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was conclusive video evidence that showed that the ball was last touched by Ariza (HOU) prior to going OOB. The ruling on the court was overturned and New Orleans was awarded possession.
Beverley (HOU) cleanly strips the ball from Holiday (NOP).
Holiday (NOP) makes incidental contact that does not affect Harden's (HOU) RSBQ. After the contact Holiday trips over his own foot causing him to fall to the ground.
Smith (HOU) maintains legal guarding position and legally contests Anderson's (NOP) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Holiday (NOP) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Harden (HOU).
Smith (HOU) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Holiday (NOP) that does not affect his RSBQ.
